    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''A Big Museum Opens, to Jeers as Well as Cheers'' (news article, Dec. 16):</p>
        <p>The discomfiture suffered by those protesting the Enola Gay installation served to invigorate this octogenarian World War II veteran's medicated heart.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''A Big Museum Opens, to Jeers as Well as Cheers'' (news article, Dec. 16):</p>
        <p>The discomfiture suffered by those protesting the Enola Gay installation served to invigorate this octogenarian World War II veteran's medicated heart.</p>
        <p>I imagined the shameful alternative of having to commemorate and mourn the loss of a million more American lives in the invasion of an unyielding, militaristic imperial Japan.</p>
        <p>It reinforced my respect for the courage and resolve of President Harry S. Truman, who put the concern for his citizen-soldiers ahead of any future revisionism of his motives, and made possible the earlier reunions of long-separated G.I.'s and their families.</p>
        <p>JOHN NOVAK  Carlsbad, Calif., Dec. 16, 2003</p>
      </block>
